Structs/DeleteModelResult.html#/s:20Lang.name: status
Structs/DeleteModelResult.html#/s:20Lang.abstract: OK indicates that the model was successfully deleted.

Structs/IdentifiedLanguages.html#/s:20La.name: languages
Structs/IdentifiedLanguages.html#/s:20La.abstract: A ranking of identified languages with confidence scores.

Structs/IdentifiableLanguages.html#/s:20.name: languages
Structs/IdentifiableLanguages.html#/s:20.abstract: A list of all languages that the service can identify.

Structs/IdentifiedLanguage.html#/s:20Lan.name: confidence
Structs/IdentifiedLanguage.html#/s:20Lan.abstract: The confidence score for the identified language.

Structs/TranslateRequest.html#/s:20Langu.name: text
Structs/TranslateRequest.html#/s:20Langu.abstract: Input text in UTF-8 encoding. It is a list so that multiple paragraphs can be submitted. Also accept a single string, instead of an array, as valid input.

Structs/TranslateRequest.html#/s:20Langu.name: modelID
Structs/TranslateRequest.html#/s:20Langu.abstract: The unique model_id of the translation model being used to translate text. The model_id inherently specifies source language, target language, and domain. If the model_id is specified, there is no need for the source and target parameters and the values are ignored.

Structs/TranslateRequest.html#/s:20Langu.name: source
Structs/TranslateRequest.html#/s:20Langu.abstract: Used in combination with target as an alternative way to select the model for translation. When target and source are set, and model_id is not set, the system chooses a default model with the right language pair to translate (usually the model based on the news domain).

Structs/TranslateRequest.html#/s:20Langu.name: target
Structs/TranslateRequest.html#/s:20Langu.abstract: Used in combination with source as an alternative way to select the model for translation. When target and source are set, and model_id is not set, the system chooses a default model with the right language pair to translate (usually the model based on the news domain).

Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.name: modelID
Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.abstract: A globally unique string that identifies the underlying model that is used for translation. This string contains all the information about source language, target language, domain, and various other related configurations.

Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.name: name
Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.abstract: If a model is trained by a user, there might be an optional “name” parameter attached during training to help the user identify the model.

Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.name: source
Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.abstract: Source language in two letter language code. Use the five letter code when clarifying between multiple supported languages. When model_id is used directly, it will override the source-target language combination. Also, when a two letter language code is used, but no suitable default is found, it returns an error.

Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.name: target
Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.abstract: Target language in two letter language code.

Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.name: baseModelID
Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.abstract: If this model is a custom model, this returns the base model that it is trained on. For a base model, this response value is empty.

Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.name: customizable
Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.abstract: Whether this model can be used as a base for customization. Customized models are not further customizable, and we don’t allow the customization of certain base models.

Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.name: defaultModel
Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.abstract: Whether this model is considered a default model and is used when the source and target languages are specified without the model_id.

Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.name: owner
Structs/TranslationModel.html#/s:20Langu.abstract: Returns the ID of the Language Translator service instance that created the model, or an empty string if it is a model that is trained by IBM.

Structs/TranslationResult.html#/s:20Lang.name: wordCount
Structs/TranslationResult.html#/s:20Lang.abstract: Number of words of the complete input text.

Structs/TranslationResult.html#/s:20Lang.name: characterCount
Structs/TranslationResult.html#/s:20Lang.abstract: Number of characters of the complete input text.

Structs/TranslationResult.html#/s:20Lang.name: translations
Structs/TranslationResult.html#/s:20Lang.abstract: List of translation output in UTF-8, corresponding to the list of input text.
